descript.abstract:
The settlmnt dataset represents the Rural Settlement areas, Industrial/Commercial areas, Commercial areas, and Rural Mixed Use Clusters that are defined in each of the official plans of the Township of North Dumfries, Township of Wilmot, Township of Wellesley, and Township of Woolwich. As well, the Towship Urban Areas (TUAs) as defined in the Regional Official Policies Plan (ROPP) are also represented.
The dataset is for convenient, general reference and DOES NOT replace the original paper documents in each of the Local Official Plans. To ensure accuracy, the orignal documents of approval should be consulted.
descript.purpose: This dataset was created to consolidate the rural settlement areas defined in the official plans of the four townships into one dataset to facilitate GIS analysis for such projects as the water/wastewater report, land budget, land use modelling, and population forecasting.
descript.supplinf: Township of Wellesley Official Plan , Township of Wilmot Official Plan, Township of Woolwich Official Plan, and Township of North Dumfries Official Plan. Region of Waterloo Regional Official Policies Plan (ROPP).

citeinfo.title: WIL_Landuse

citeinfo.title: WEL_Landuse
citeinfo.othercit: This dataset represents the spatial extents of approved land use designations put forth in the Township of Wellesley Official Plan (September, 2003) and all mapping amendments.

citeinfo.title: WOO_Landuse
citeinfo.othercit: This dataset represents the spatial extents of approved land use designations put forth in the Township of Woolwich Official Plan (May 8, 2002) and all mapping amendments.

dataqual.logic: The dataset has been evaluated for overlapping polygons and is topologically correct. It is snapped to the parcel fabric where possible or brought to road centerlines where appropriate.
dataqual.complete:
The data is current as of the last consolidation of each Local Official Plan and incorporates all Official Plan Amendments approved since then that have had an impact on the setllement area boundaries.
The dataset is for convenient, general reference and DOES NOT replace the original paper documents found in each Local Official Plan or Regional Official Polices Plan. To ensure accuracy, the original documents of approval should be consulted.

horizpa.horizpar: There has been some level of interpretation due to scaling issues of the paper originals.

procstep.procdesc: Digital datasets representing the individual township settlement boundaries were snapped to the parcel fabric where possible and the hardcopy maps available in each Local Area OP were used as a verification of the location of the settlement boundary. As well, the boundary was modified if there was an amendment to the local OP.
Modfied the Ayr urban boundary as a result of the approval of the Township of North Dumfries Official Plan Amendment #10 which came into effect 2008-12-24.
Modified the Sunfish Lake settlement area as a result of Wilmot OPA # 5 that came into effect 2009-07-09
Brought the portion of the Merlin Jutzi property that came into the urban area as part of the ROP

dataIdInfo.idAbs: The settllements dataset represents the Rural Settlement areas, Industrial/Commercial areas, Commercial areas, and Rural Mixed Use Clusters that are defined in each of the official plans of the Township of North Dumfries, Township of Wilmot, Township of Wellesley, and Township of Woolwich. As well, the Towship Urban Areas (TUAs) as defined in the Regional Official Policies Plan (ROPP) are also represented. The dataset is for convenient, general reference and DOES NOT replace the original paper documents in each of the Local Official Plans. To ensure accuracy, the orignal documents of approval should be consulted.(Last edited 2012-11-22)

report.evalMethDesc: The dataset has been evaluated for overlapping polygons and is topologically correct. It is snapped to the parcel fabric where possible or brought to road centerlines where appropriate.

report.measDesc: The dataset has been evaluated for overlapping polygons and is topologically correct. It is snapped to the parcel fabric where possible or brought to road centerlines where appropriate.

The data is current as of the last consolidation of each Local Official Plan and incorporates all Official Plan Amendments approved since then that have had an impact on the setllement area boundaries. The dataset is for convenient, general reference and DOES NOT replace the original paper documents found in each Local Official Plan or Regional Official Polices Plan. To ensure accuracy, the original documents of approval should be consulted.
There has been some level of interpretation due to scaling issues of the paper originals.

prcStep.stepDesc: Modfied the Ayr urban boundary as a result of the approval of the Township of North Dumfries Official Plan Amendment #10 which came into effect 2008-12-24.
Modified the Sunfish Lake settlement area as a result of Wilmot OPA # 5 that came into effect 2009-07-09

Digital datasets representing the individual township settlement boundaries were snapped to the parcel fabric where possible and the hardcopy maps available in each Local Area OP were used as a verification of the location of the settlement boundary. As well, the boundary was modified if there was an amendment to the local OP.
Brought the portion of the Merlin Jutzi property that came into the urban area as part of the ROP
